import re
#Use of IP or not in domain
def having_ip_address(URLs):
    match = re.search(
        '(([01]?\\d\\d?|2[0-4]\\d|25[0-5])\\.([01]?\\d\\d?|2[0-4]\\d|25[0-5])\\.([01]?\\d\\d?|2[0-4]\\d|25[0-5])\\.'
        '([01]?\\d\\d?|2[0-4]\\d|25[0-5])\\/)|'  # IPv4
        '((0x[0-9a-fA-F]{1,2})\\.(0x[0-9a-fA-F]{1,2})\\.(0x[0-9a-fA-F]{1,2})\\.(0x[0-9a-fA-F]{1,2})\\/)' # IPv4 in hexadecimal
        '(?:[a-fA-F0-9]{1,4}:){7}[a-fA-F0-9]{1,4}', URLs)  # Ipv6
    if match:
        # print match.group()
        return 1
    else:
        # print 'No matching pattern found'
        return 0
df['use_of_ip'] = df['URLs'].apply(lambda i: having_ip_address(i))

def google_index(URLs):
    site = search(URLs, 5)
    return 1 if site else 0
df['google_index'] = df['URLs'].apply(lambda i: google_index(i))

from urllib.parse import urlparse
def count_www(URLs):
    URLs.count('www')
    return URLs.count('www')

df['count-www'] = df['URLs'].apply(lambda i: count_www(i))

def count_atrate(URLs):
     
    return URLs.count('@')

df['count@'] = df['URLs'].apply(lambda i: count_atrate(i))


def no_of_dir(URLs):
    urldir = urlparse(URLs).path
    return urldir.count('/')

df['count_dir'] = df['URLs'].apply(lambda i: no_of_dir(i))

def no_of_embed(URLs):
    urldir = urlparse(URLs).path
    return urldir.count('//')

df['count_embed_domian'] = df['URLs'].apply(lambda i: no_of_embed(i))


def shortening_service(URLs):
    match = re.search('bit\.ly|goo\.gl|shorte\.st|go2l\.ink|x\.co|ow\.ly|t\.co|tinyurl|tr\.im|is\.gd|cli\.gs|'
                      'yfrog\.com|migre\.me|ff\.im|tiny\.cc|url4\.eu|twit\.ac|su\.pr|twurl\.nl|snipurl\.com|'
                      'short\.to|BudURL\.com|ping\.fm|post\.ly|Just\.as|bkite\.com|snipr\.com|fic\.kr|loopt\.us|'
                      'doiop\.com|short\.ie|kl\.am|wp\.me|rubyurl\.com|om\.ly|to\.ly|bit\.do|t\.co|lnkd\.in|'
                      'db\.tt|qr\.ae|adf\.ly|goo\.gl|bitly\.com|cur\.lv|tinyurl\.com|ow\.ly|bit\.ly|ity\.im|'
                      'q\.gs|is\.gd|po\.st|bc\.vc|twitthis\.com|u\.to|j\.mp|buzurl\.com|cutt\.us|u\.bb|yourls\.org|'
                      'x\.co|prettylinkpro\.com|scrnch\.me|filoops\.info|vzturl\.com|qr\.net|1url\.com|tweez\.me|v\.gd|'
                      'tr\.im|link\.zip\.net',
                      URLs)
    if match:
        return 1
    else:
        return 0
    
    
df['short_url'] = df['URLs'].apply(lambda i: shortening_service(i))

    return URLs.count('?')

df['count?'] = df['URLs'].apply(lambda i: count_ques(i))

def count_hyphen(URLs):
    return URLs.count('-')

df['count-'] = df['URLs'].apply(lambda i: count_hyphen(i))

def count_equal(URLs):
    return URLs.count('=')

df['count='] = df['URLs'].apply(lambda i: count_equal(i))

def url_length(URLs):
    return len(str(URLs))


#Length of URL
df['url_length'] = df['URLs'].apply(lambda i: url_length(i))
#Hostname Length

def hostname_length(URLs):
    return len(urlparse(URLs).netloc)

df['hostname_length'] = df['URLs'].apply(lambda i: hostname_length(i))

df.head()

def suspicious_words(URLs):
    match = re.search('PayPal|login|signin|bank|account|update|free|lucky|service|bonus|ebayisapi|webscr',
                      URLs)
    if match:
        return 1
    else:
        return 0
df['sus_url'] = df['URLs'].apply(lambda i: suspicious_words(i))


def digit_count(URLs):
    digits = 0
    for i in URLs:
        if i.isnumeric():
            digits = digits + 1
    return digits


df['count-digits']= df['URLs'].apply(lambda i: digit_count(i))


def letter_count(URLs):
    letters = 0
    for i in URLs:
        if i.isalpha():
            letters = letters + 1
    return letters


df['count-letters']= df['URLs'].apply(lambda i: letter_count(i))

#Importing dependencies
from urllib.parse import urlparse
from tld import get_tld
import os.path

#First Directory Length
def fd_length(URLs):
    urlpath= urlparse(URLs).path
    try:
        return len(urlpath.split('/')[1])
    except:
        return 0

df['fd_length'] = df['URLs'].apply(lambda i: fd_length(i))

#Length of Top Level Domain
df['tld'] = df['URLs'].apply(lambda i: get_tld(i,fail_silently=True))


def tld_length(tld):
    try:
        return len(tld)
    except:
        return -1

df['tld_length'] = df['tld'].apply(lambda i: tld_length(i))

In [62]:
def main(url):
    
    status = []
    
    status.append(having_ip_address(url))
    
    status.append(count_dot(url))
    status.append(count_www(url))
    status.append(count_atrate(url))
    status.append(no_of_dir(url))
    status.append(no_of_embed(url))
    
    status.append(shortening_service(url))
    status.append(count_https(url))
    status.append(count_http(url))
    
    status.append(count_per(url))
    status.append(count_ques(url))
    status.append(count_hyphen(url))
    status.append(count_equal(url))
    
    status.append(url_length(url))
    status.append(hostname_length(url))
    status.append(suspicious_words(url))
    status.append(digit_count(url))
    status.append(letter_count(url))
    status.append(fd_length(url))
    tld = get_tld(url,fail_silently=True)
      
    status.append(tld_length(tld))
    
    
    

    return status
In [63]:
def get_prediction_from_url(test_url):
    features_test = main(test_url)
    # Due to updates to scikit-learn, we now need a 2D array as a parameter to the predict function.
    features_test = np.array(features_test).reshape((1, -1))

    

    pred = rf.predict(features_test)
    if int(pred[0]) == 0:
        
        res="SAFE"
        return res
        
    elif int(pred[0]) == 1.0:
        
        res="PHISHING"
        return res
